9
00:01:50,965 --> 00:01:52,133
I…

10
00:01:53,426 --> 00:01:54,844
I must have missed something.

11
00:01:56,596 --> 00:01:57,889
Don't be silly.

12
00:01:57,972 --> 00:01:59,849
We ran dozens of clinical trials.

13
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:01,351
There weren't any issues.

14
00:02:01,434 --> 00:02:03,728
We carried out
strict safety tests as well.

15
00:02:03,811 --> 00:02:06,064
I can't believe this.

16
00:02:06,981 --> 00:02:08,650
I feel like it's all my fault.

17
00:02:08,733 --> 00:02:10,777
No, Hae-seok.

18
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:12,654
Your recipe was flawless.

19
00:02:12,737 --> 00:02:15,490
If there were any issues with the cream,

20
00:02:16,157 --> 00:02:19,035
it's the CEO's fault
for not managing everything well.

21
00:02:19,577 --> 00:02:20,495
I'm to blame.

22
00:02:20,578 --> 00:02:21,788
Woo-su,

23
00:02:22,413 --> 00:02:23,915
I'm going back to the factory.

24
00:02:23,998 --> 00:02:25,333
I need to check again.

25
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:26,626
Hae-seok.

26
00:02:26,709 --> 00:02:28,461
You've done your part.

27
00:02:29,629 --> 00:02:30,838
This is my responsibility now.

28
00:02:32,173 --> 00:02:33,216
All of you, just wait.

29
00:02:33,299 --> 00:02:35,218
I'm going to look into this.

30
00:02:39,931 --> 00:02:41,474
Woo-su!

31
00:02:41,557 --> 00:02:43,434
I feel like this is my fault.

32
00:02:44,143 --> 00:02:45,478
So let me go and--

33
00:02:45,561 --> 00:02:47,063
Hae-seok,

34
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:50,233
we need to focus on the bigger picture.

35
00:02:51,901 --> 00:02:54,529
You have so many things
to do in the future.

36
00:02:54,612 --> 00:02:56,280
Still, I--

37
00:02:56,364 --> 00:02:58,032
I trust you.

38
00:03:00,326 --> 00:03:01,452
You trust me too, right?

39
00:03:05,581 --> 00:03:06,833
We'll fix this.

40
00:03:27,103 --> 00:03:28,354
SLEEP MEDICATION

41
00:03:28,438 --> 00:03:30,982
WOO-SU, WHAT'S GOING ON?
PLEASE ANSWER ME

42
00:03:42,785 --> 00:03:44,037
MU-WON

43
00:03:46,205 --> 00:03:47,206
Mu-won.

44
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:49,083
<i>Hae-seok, have you been</i>
<i>in touch with Woo-su?</i>

45
00:03:50,084 --> 00:03:51,502
No, I haven't.

46
00:03:52,337 --> 00:03:53,588
He's not answering you either?

47
00:03:53,671 --> 00:03:55,965
<i>He turned off his phone.</i>
<i>Where the hell did he go?</i>

48
00:03:56,549 --> 00:04:00,178
<i>His mother can't reach him either.</i>
<i>Let me know if you get in touch with him.</i>

49
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:33,503
Woo-su…

50
00:04:34,754 --> 00:04:35,755
Woo-su…

51
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:49,560
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

52
00:04:50,645 --> 00:04:53,398
<i>Everything was my fault.</i>

53
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:19,298
Hae-seok, Chang-ho is here.

54
00:05:36,566 --> 00:05:37,733
Come here.

55
00:05:37,817 --> 00:05:39,819
Let's stay with Woo-su together.

56
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:43,948
Woo-su…

57
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:47,243
Woo-su…

58
00:05:48,995 --> 00:05:50,746
switched the raw materials.

59
00:05:52,206 --> 00:05:54,083
He even fabricated…

60
00:05:55,251 --> 00:05:57,420
all the clinical trial results…

61
00:05:59,589 --> 00:06:01,424
What are you talking about?

62
00:06:01,507 --> 00:06:02,925
It was all because of money…

63
00:06:04,594 --> 00:06:06,971
That jerk stabbed us in the back…

64
00:06:07,597 --> 00:06:09,891
just because of some money.

65
00:06:15,146 --> 00:06:16,189
Woo-su.

66
00:06:16,814 --> 00:06:17,690
Why did you do that?

67
00:06:18,232 --> 00:06:20,026
-Why?
-Chang-ho, stop.

68
00:06:20,109 --> 00:06:21,235
Why did you do that?

69
00:06:21,319 --> 00:06:22,653
-Don't do this right now!
-Why?

70
00:06:22,737 --> 00:06:24,363
Why the hell did you do that?

71
00:06:24,447 --> 00:06:25,740
Get a grip!

72
00:06:25,823 --> 00:06:26,699
-Why?
-Chang-ho!

73
00:06:26,782 --> 00:06:29,160
Why would you do that?

74
00:07:40,189 --> 00:07:47,154
PERHAPS WE CAN SEE
THE RAINY SEASON TOGETHER

75
00:07:56,122 --> 00:07:57,123
Ye-jin.

76
00:08:03,087 --> 00:08:05,298
I told you it's fine.

77
00:08:05,798 --> 00:08:07,675
All done.

78
00:08:07,758 --> 00:08:09,385
Just eat a little bit.

79
00:08:09,468 --> 00:08:10,595
That's hot.

80
00:08:11,554 --> 00:08:13,306
-Are you okay?
-I'm fine.

81
00:08:14,015 --> 00:08:14,890
Eat up.

82
00:08:16,434 --> 00:08:17,810
Go on. Eat.

83
00:08:18,894 --> 00:08:19,979
Thanks.

84
00:08:28,654 --> 00:08:29,655
Are you doing okay?

85
00:08:33,909 --> 00:08:37,288
You must be tired after your trip.

86
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,501
Am I the kind of person

87
00:08:43,461 --> 00:08:45,046
people get tired of?

88
00:08:48,674 --> 00:08:50,259
Everyone leaves if I show them love.

89
00:08:51,010 --> 00:08:53,387
What are you talking about?

90
00:08:55,306 --> 00:08:56,349
Ye-jin.

91
00:08:57,183 --> 00:08:58,476
I need some rest.

92
00:08:59,393 --> 00:09:00,936
Sorry. I'll clean this up later.

93
00:09:20,831 --> 00:09:22,583
<i>It's suffocating.</i>

94
00:09:23,584 --> 00:09:25,711
I feel suffocated when I'm with you.

95
00:09:51,987 --> 00:09:53,989
-You ruined our lives.
-You said we could trust it.

96
00:09:54,073 --> 00:09:56,283
-You already let go of your guilt.
-How can you do this?

97
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:58,661
-It hurts!
-I'll hate you for the rest of my life!

98
00:10:00,162 --> 00:10:01,789
I'm sorry, Hae-seok…

99
00:10:14,927 --> 00:10:15,845
SLEEP MEDICATION

100
00:10:48,335 --> 00:10:51,255
-Hey, Mechoori!
-Mechoori!

101
00:10:51,338 --> 00:10:52,465
I bet you haven't heard yet.

102
00:10:52,548 --> 00:10:56,677
Ms. Dam sent us an incredible gift!

103
00:10:56,761 --> 00:10:58,137
Mechoori, look at this.

104
00:10:58,804 --> 00:11:02,516
She sent us a huge TV
and really expensive-looking speakers.

105
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:06,812
Our community center
practically looks like a theater now!

106
00:11:06,896 --> 00:11:08,189
And…

107
00:11:08,272 --> 00:11:09,857
there's a message here too. Read it.

108
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,233
I FELT SO WARM HERE
THANK YOU

109
00:11:14,195 --> 00:11:15,654
That's great.

110
00:11:17,364 --> 00:11:18,908
"That's great"?

111
00:11:19,492 --> 00:11:21,160
-My gosh.
-It is great.

112
00:11:21,243 --> 00:11:24,955
I haven't seen her recently.
I guess she returned to Seoul.

113
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:27,124
This must be really expensive.
We're so grateful.

114
00:11:28,292 --> 00:11:30,961
Whenever Ms. Dam does a broadcast,

115
00:11:31,045 --> 00:11:33,464
we're all going to gather
and watch it together.

116
00:11:33,547 --> 00:11:34,632
Of course.

117
00:11:34,715 --> 00:11:36,133
-Not you.
-You stay away.

118
00:11:36,217 --> 00:11:37,635
Just stay home.

119
00:11:38,802 --> 00:11:39,970
Watch wrestling or something.

120
00:11:40,054 --> 00:11:41,847
WORK

121
00:12:08,290 --> 00:12:09,625
DAM YE-JIN IS BACK!

122
00:12:12,419 --> 00:12:13,629
Ms. Dam.

123
00:12:13,712 --> 00:12:15,589
Let's stick together

124
00:12:15,673 --> 00:12:17,174
from now on…

125
00:12:17,258 --> 00:12:18,717
Hey, stop.

126
00:12:18,801 --> 00:12:20,719
Seeing people cry makes me cry too.

127
00:12:22,221 --> 00:12:24,932
Mr. Hwang. Sung-mi.

128
00:12:25,683 --> 00:12:27,226
Thank you so much.

129
00:12:29,186 --> 00:12:30,813
Let's get to work.

130
00:12:32,523 --> 00:12:33,607
Let's do this.

131
00:12:48,706 --> 00:12:51,417
The hotel vacation package
seems to be the best item.

132
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,668
Right?

133
00:12:52,751 --> 00:12:55,671
I struggled so hard not to lose this item.

134
00:12:57,631 --> 00:13:00,259
We've worked hard, so let's head home now.

135
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:02,553
You guys go ahead.

136
00:13:02,636 --> 00:13:04,722
What? We need to celebrate your first day.

137
00:13:04,805 --> 00:13:07,057
Then I'll find a great place to go.

138
00:13:07,141 --> 00:13:08,642
Okay.

139
00:13:09,268 --> 00:13:12,479
Recommend a nice restaurant nearby
with at least a 4.5-rating

140
00:13:12,563 --> 00:13:14,565
that sells Korean or Western food.

141
00:13:14,648 --> 00:13:16,066
Exclude places with long lines.

142
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:18,068
And make sure parking is easy.

143
00:13:19,153 --> 00:13:20,029
Cue.

144
00:13:20,112 --> 00:13:22,072
<i>I recommend Garamchae</i>
<i>with traditional Korean food</i>

145
00:13:22,156 --> 00:13:25,075
<i>and the Italian restaurant Fiore Garden.</i>

146
00:13:25,826 --> 00:13:29,747
<i>Both restaurants</i>
<i>are approximately a 10-minute drive away.</i>

147
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:31,290
We can go to one of these.

148
00:13:31,373 --> 00:13:32,833
Hey, which do you prefer?

149
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:33,792
Korean? Or Italian?

150
00:13:34,418 --> 00:13:35,878
Let's go next time.

151
00:13:35,961 --> 00:13:36,837
Hey.

152
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,756
Get up while I'm asking nicely.

153
00:13:38,839 --> 00:13:42,092
You saw how everyone's talking about me.

154
00:13:42,176 --> 00:13:43,302
I can't.

155
00:13:47,097 --> 00:13:48,432
Then don't overdo it,

156
00:13:48,515 --> 00:13:50,517
unless you want
striped maple extract again.

157
00:13:50,601 --> 00:13:51,435
All right.

158
00:13:52,019 --> 00:13:54,146
Go on. I'll see you tomorrow.

159
00:13:54,229 --> 00:13:55,147
See you tomorrow.

160
00:13:55,773 --> 00:13:56,815
-We're going, then.
-Okay.

161
00:13:56,899 --> 00:13:58,400
What would you like? Italian? Korean?

162
00:13:58,484 --> 00:13:59,401
Let's go and see.

163
00:13:59,485 --> 00:14:00,986
Join us if you get hungry later.

164
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:02,446
Okay. Bye.

165
00:14:02,529 --> 00:14:03,405
Bye.

166
00:14:22,466 --> 00:14:25,344
Mr. Cha, what are you doing?

167
00:14:30,975 --> 00:14:32,059
You're here.

168
00:14:37,398 --> 00:14:38,232
Give it to him.

169
00:14:43,529 --> 00:14:45,489
The minutes
from the shareholders' meeting.

170
00:14:46,073 --> 00:14:49,284
The proposal to dismiss you was approved.

171
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:53,163
No need to say it
in such complicated words.

172
00:14:53,998 --> 00:14:55,499
You mean I'm fired, right?

173
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:58,460
You should've just kept living
the way you were.

174
00:14:59,128 --> 00:15:00,671
You just had to ruin things.

175
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,675
No, I realized how I should live

176
00:15:04,758 --> 00:15:05,801
thanks to you.

177
00:15:08,512 --> 00:15:11,056
I'll take care of everything here,
so just go home.

178
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:13,517
You'd better lie low for a while.

179
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,561
We can't brush this off
as immaturity this time.

180
00:15:17,771 --> 00:15:19,690
Thanks for the concern,

181
00:15:19,773 --> 00:15:20,816
but I'll handle it myself.

182
00:15:22,735 --> 00:15:24,111
You're not saying

183
00:15:25,237 --> 00:15:27,072
you want to stay in Korea, are you?

184
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:32,494
Is it because of that host?

185
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:34,913
And if I say yes?

186
00:15:35,456 --> 00:15:36,915
Will you steal her away from me too?

187
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:38,709
What?

188
00:15:39,209 --> 00:15:40,085
Bye, then.

189
00:15:47,509 --> 00:15:48,719
What?

190
00:16:00,481 --> 00:16:02,357
You've changed quite a bit.

191
00:16:02,983 --> 00:16:04,651
You're putting me in a tough spot.

192
00:16:05,235 --> 00:16:08,572
This was the only way to meet you.

193
00:16:10,908 --> 00:16:11,950
Just get to the point.

194
00:16:15,287 --> 00:16:16,830
As you probably guessed,

195
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:19,917
I'm here because of Ye-jin.

196
00:16:22,169 --> 00:16:23,545
Ye-jin's…

197
00:16:25,214 --> 00:16:26,548
still in a lot of pain.

198
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,594
So?

199
00:16:32,054 --> 00:16:33,472
Couldn't you try…

200
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,934
reaching out to Ye-jin first?

201
00:16:40,562 --> 00:16:42,689
You should've thought
once more before coming here.

202
00:16:44,274 --> 00:16:46,151
Then you would've known I'd refuse.

203
00:16:49,029 --> 00:16:50,072
Just go.

204
00:16:50,823 --> 00:16:52,574
And don't come here ever again.

205
00:16:53,784 --> 00:16:57,121
Do you still have the wrong idea
about what happened five years ago?

206
00:16:57,204 --> 00:17:00,332
The wrong idea? She told me herself
that she was getting revenge.

207
00:17:00,415 --> 00:17:02,835
Are you sure you didn't push her
to say that?

208
00:17:05,129 --> 00:17:07,172
Do you think it was Ye-jin

209
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:09,633
who said that,

210
00:17:10,843 --> 00:17:12,553
or your heart?

211
00:17:14,805 --> 00:17:16,265
Ye-jin

212
00:17:16,849 --> 00:17:18,475
isn't someone who'd do that.

213
00:17:20,144 --> 00:17:22,312
Think about it carefully, Myeong-hwa.

214
00:17:28,569 --> 00:17:30,237
You really believe such stupid gossip?

215
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,488
What if it isn't just gossip?

216
00:17:31,572 --> 00:17:33,866
You're at the edge of a cliff.

217
00:17:33,949 --> 00:17:35,993
Losing a few roles
isn't the problem right now.

218
00:17:36,076 --> 00:17:38,412
You might be forced out
of the industry altogether.

219
00:17:40,539 --> 00:17:43,083
Whether I fall from that cliff or not,

220
00:17:43,709 --> 00:17:44,710
I'm…

221
00:17:46,587 --> 00:17:47,838
taking responsibility for this.

222
00:17:47,921 --> 00:17:53,677
<i>As of today, I shall retire</i>
<i>from my acting career.</i>

223
00:17:55,470 --> 00:17:58,473
<i>I told you it wasn't just gossip!</i>

224
00:17:58,557 --> 00:18:01,185
<i>Dam Ye-jin really received hush money!</i>

225
00:18:04,605 --> 00:18:05,480
Ms. Song.

226
00:18:05,564 --> 00:18:08,025
Ms. Ji, what brings you here?

227
00:18:08,108 --> 00:18:09,318
I came to join forces.

228
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:11,320
Join forces?

229
00:18:12,529 --> 00:18:15,782
Dam Ye-jin returned to HIT today.

230
00:18:15,866 --> 00:18:17,784
To be precise, it's her second return.

231
00:18:17,868 --> 00:18:19,119
Honestly,

232
00:18:19,203 --> 00:18:21,997
after what happened with L'Étoile,
something about her feels off.

233
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:25,083
How is she always causing
scandals like this?

234
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:26,168
Don't you think?

235
00:18:26,752 --> 00:18:28,337
-Ms. Ji.
-Yes?

236
00:18:28,420 --> 00:18:29,922
I'm just curious,

237
00:18:30,547 --> 00:18:33,425
why do you hate
Dam Ye-jin so much, Ms. Ji?

238
00:18:57,157 --> 00:18:58,492
What about Mr. Hwang?

239
00:18:58,575 --> 00:19:00,994
We just parted
because someone killed the mood.

240
00:19:02,913 --> 00:19:05,540
I just came to kill you with kindness,

241
00:19:05,624 --> 00:19:06,667
so eat up.

242
00:19:15,384 --> 00:19:16,760
You're a workaholic

243
00:19:16,843 --> 00:19:18,929
doing the work that you love so much,

244
00:19:19,012 --> 00:19:21,306
but why do you look so down?

245
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:24,935
Is your heart elsewhere right now?

246
00:19:25,018 --> 00:19:26,061
What is it?

247
00:19:32,359 --> 00:19:34,403
I broke up with him.

248
00:19:37,656 --> 00:19:38,865
Why?

249
00:19:38,949 --> 00:19:40,617
Why did you get dumped?

250
00:19:44,121 --> 00:19:45,872
Did you really get dumped?

251
00:19:45,956 --> 00:19:47,291
Why did I get that right?

252
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:49,042
Are you okay?

253
00:19:52,212 --> 00:19:54,339
I want to be fine,

254
00:19:56,425 --> 00:19:59,928
but I feel like there's a hole inside me.

255
00:20:00,554 --> 00:20:02,973
What happened?

256
00:20:03,056 --> 00:20:04,057
He…

257
00:20:05,976 --> 00:20:09,062
was the researcher
who made Good Morning Cream.

258
00:20:12,566 --> 00:20:13,442
Really?

259
00:20:16,069 --> 00:20:17,237
He told me himself.

260
00:20:17,863 --> 00:20:20,532
But why did he tell you now
after all this time?

261
00:20:20,615 --> 00:20:21,742
What about you?

262
00:20:21,825 --> 00:20:22,909
Sung-mi.

263
00:20:25,787 --> 00:20:27,497
I have no idea…

264
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:31,460
how he truly feels.

265
00:20:52,981 --> 00:20:55,192
DAM YE-JIN

266
00:21:09,331 --> 00:21:10,791
<i>Mom…</i>

267
00:21:13,502 --> 00:21:15,337
I thought

268
00:21:16,213 --> 00:21:19,257
I'd stop thinking about him and be okay

269
00:21:19,925 --> 00:21:22,469
once I went back to work,

270
00:21:23,345 --> 00:21:25,097
but I can't.

271
00:21:27,516 --> 00:21:29,351
<i>He said…</i>

272
00:21:30,894 --> 00:21:33,939
<i>that everything he showed me</i>

273
00:21:34,022 --> 00:21:36,233
<i>and all the moments we spent together</i>

274
00:21:37,192 --> 00:21:39,236
<i>were a lie.</i>

275
00:21:40,487 --> 00:21:41,947
<i>But,</i>

276
00:21:43,323 --> 00:21:46,743
<i>he seemed to be in more pain than me</i>

277
00:21:47,661 --> 00:21:49,538
<i>as he said that.</i>

278
00:21:52,332 --> 00:21:53,625
<i>I don't know.</i>

279
00:21:54,418 --> 00:21:58,338
<i>I have no idea…</i>

280
00:21:59,923 --> 00:22:01,341
But…

281
00:22:03,093 --> 00:22:08,515
I want to hear what's really on his mind.

282
00:22:25,282 --> 00:22:27,409
Hey! Mechoori!

283
00:22:27,492 --> 00:22:28,910
What's wrong? Did you cut yourself?

284
00:22:30,453 --> 00:22:31,997
Oh, no! Hey!

285
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:33,748
-Let's get that treated.
-I'm fine.

286
00:22:33,832 --> 00:22:37,127
Don't be silly. What's up with you?
This isn't like you at all.

287
00:22:37,836 --> 00:22:39,045
Hey…

288
00:22:39,129 --> 00:22:40,463
I'll go to the hospital.

289
00:22:49,973 --> 00:22:54,311
<i>I'm not sure why you're asking</i>
<i>for sleep medication again…</i>

290
00:22:55,103 --> 00:22:57,397
<i>but you really shouldn't</i>

291
00:22:57,480 --> 00:23:00,609
<i>overuse them like last time,</i>

292
00:23:00,692 --> 00:23:01,735
<i>all right?</i>

293
00:23:05,822 --> 00:23:09,117
Jin-yi, are you closed today?

294
00:23:09,201 --> 00:23:11,578
I'll be back soon after I take Som-yi
to the hospital.

295
00:23:11,661 --> 00:23:13,663
Right, she's getting treated.

296
00:23:13,747 --> 00:23:17,250
So many young kids here
seem unwell these days.

297
00:23:17,334 --> 00:23:20,712
Som-yi's sick,
and Mechoori's looking so down…

298
00:23:20,795 --> 00:23:22,631
Do you know what's going on?

299
00:23:22,714 --> 00:23:24,132
Mechoori

300
00:23:24,216 --> 00:23:26,843
-broke up with Ms. Dam, didn't he?
-He can't have.

301
00:23:26,927 --> 00:23:28,970
-I'm sure he did.
-No way.

302
00:23:29,054 --> 00:23:30,472
I'm sure of it! Hey!

303
00:23:30,555 --> 00:23:32,766
-Bye.
-They must've broken up.

304
00:23:32,849 --> 00:23:34,434
I'm sure of it.

305
00:23:38,563 --> 00:23:41,024
It's going to take ages
going to the hospital by bus.

306
00:23:41,942 --> 00:23:44,736
Can't we just ask Mechoori for a ride?

307
00:23:44,819 --> 00:23:46,112
Don't you dare contact him.

308
00:23:46,196 --> 00:23:47,948
Geez.

309
00:23:48,031 --> 00:23:49,324
Hey! It's Mechoori!

310
00:23:51,576 --> 00:23:53,119
Mechoori!

311
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:55,372
Hey, get back out here.

312
00:23:56,831 --> 00:23:57,707
I'll give you a ride.

313
00:24:01,336 --> 00:24:04,464
Just until Som-yi's treatment is over.

314
00:24:04,547 --> 00:24:06,967
You shouldn't drive
with your hand like that.

315
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:08,385
Just stop. Live your own life.

316
00:24:08,468 --> 00:24:09,678
Jin-yi.

317
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:12,472
It's the least I can do.

318
00:24:13,014 --> 00:24:13,932
Just let me help.

319
00:24:15,517 --> 00:24:17,727
You really have a way
of making me uncomfortable.

320
00:24:39,624 --> 00:24:42,877
The factory manager won't be here today.

321
00:24:49,634 --> 00:24:53,221
Can I ask why you're trying
to get in touch with him?

322
00:24:55,056 --> 00:24:56,057
I have to find out

323
00:24:56,141 --> 00:24:59,352
who made the order to have microbes

324
00:24:59,436 --> 00:25:00,520
added to the essence.

325
00:25:01,396 --> 00:25:02,814
You won't be able to…

326
00:25:03,481 --> 00:25:07,652
find evidence
that this was ordered by the deputy CEO.

327
00:25:10,613 --> 00:25:12,532
You're saying it's meaningless anyway?

328
00:25:13,074 --> 00:25:15,952
Are you telling me to do nothing?

329
00:25:16,036 --> 00:25:17,078
No,

330
00:25:20,248 --> 00:25:21,791
I'm suggesting we do this together.

331
00:25:24,419 --> 00:25:26,755
Why would you join me?

332
00:25:26,838 --> 00:25:29,674
From what I've seen all these years,

333
00:25:30,508 --> 00:25:32,761
even when you wanted something,
you never showed it,

334
00:25:33,678 --> 00:25:35,388
and even what little you had

335
00:25:36,473 --> 00:25:39,100
were things
that Ms. Michelle had thrown away.

336
00:25:43,146 --> 00:25:44,731
Including me.

337
00:25:44,814 --> 00:25:47,567
You're fired. Get out!

338
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:50,862
Do you not understand? Get out, you jerk!

339
00:26:05,585 --> 00:26:08,004
Why don't you assist me from now on?

340
00:26:11,716 --> 00:26:14,386
<i>If there's anything I can do</i>

341
00:26:14,469 --> 00:26:16,054
<i>to help in this position I owe to you,</i>

342
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:21,142
I'd like to,
even though it's already late.

343
00:26:24,771 --> 00:26:27,649
Are you sure about this?

344
00:26:28,691 --> 00:26:30,610
I've made up my mind.

345
00:26:36,825 --> 00:26:38,868
I know I should refuse,

346
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:43,748
but you're the only one
I can trust right now.

347
00:26:53,007 --> 00:26:55,051
Jung-muk!

348
00:26:55,135 --> 00:26:57,470
Jung-muk!

349
00:26:57,971 --> 00:26:59,806
Jung-muk!

350
00:27:00,390 --> 00:27:01,724
Jung-muk!

351
00:27:01,808 --> 00:27:03,184
Jung-muk!

352
00:27:03,268 --> 00:27:05,353
Jung-muk!

353
00:27:05,437 --> 00:27:06,312
I need a diagnosis.

354
00:27:07,689 --> 00:27:08,690
What is it this time?

355
00:27:08,773 --> 00:27:10,942
I bought a ton of her products,
like you told me.

356
00:27:11,025 --> 00:27:12,444
But why is she reacting like this?

357
00:27:12,527 --> 00:27:14,821
She hasn't been replying since yesterday!

358
00:27:14,904 --> 00:27:16,448
You were lacking effort.

359
00:27:16,531 --> 00:27:17,407
Effort?

360
00:27:17,490 --> 00:27:19,409
You should've written a review.

361
00:27:22,036 --> 00:27:23,455
I was so stupid.

362
00:27:23,538 --> 00:27:25,248
I didn't even think of that.

363
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,000
Thanks.

364
00:27:27,083 --> 00:27:28,334
I'll treat you to some meat!

365
00:27:30,837 --> 00:27:31,838
Aren't you dating anyone?

366
00:27:36,801 --> 00:27:39,012
I have no idea what's on his mind.

367
00:27:41,973 --> 00:27:43,766
I bought some!

368
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:45,226
Order complete!

369
00:27:45,310 --> 00:27:48,563
Organic goat milk powder from Kilimanjaro!

370
00:27:48,646 --> 00:27:50,773
User review!

371
00:27:50,857 --> 00:27:53,151
If I sent a selfie,
he could've at least sent one back.

372
00:27:53,234 --> 00:27:55,737
But he suddenly bought our products
and sent his purchase form.

373
00:27:55,820 --> 00:27:57,572
And now, he even sent a review.

374
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:01,701
I feel like I've become
a pyramid scheme salesperson.

375
00:28:05,705 --> 00:28:07,207
Is he trying to draw a line?

376
00:28:08,041 --> 00:28:11,836
But men don't spend their money and time
on women they're not interested in.

377
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:14,047
-Right.
-And he's spending it on you.

378
00:28:14,130 --> 00:28:15,840
And a lot.

379
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:20,887
Are you saying he's interested or not?

380
00:28:20,970 --> 00:28:23,348
Then what about
when you're talking on the phone?

381
00:28:23,431 --> 00:28:26,851
He gets really chatty on the phone.

382
00:28:26,935 --> 00:28:30,355
He talks about his village
and the mushroom farm and stuff.

383
00:28:33,525 --> 00:28:34,526
What?

384
00:28:35,026 --> 00:28:36,194
Why did you suddenly stop?

385
00:28:38,404 --> 00:28:40,114
Is everything okay over there?

386
00:28:41,074 --> 00:28:42,534
I should be asking that about you.

387
00:28:54,128 --> 00:28:55,171
Yes, Mr. Cha.

388
00:28:55,255 --> 00:28:58,132
I should've taken you there. I'm sorry.

389
00:28:58,216 --> 00:29:00,468
Ms. Michelle suddenly summoned me.

390
00:29:01,010 --> 00:29:02,095
What for?

391
00:29:02,178 --> 00:29:05,265
<i>She wanted coffee</i>
<i>as hot as the core of the sun.</i>

392
00:29:05,974 --> 00:29:08,268
She must think she's Miranda
from <i>The Devil Wears Prada</i>

393
00:29:08,351 --> 00:29:09,477
or something.

394
00:29:09,561 --> 00:29:12,397
Michelle, Miranda…
Those "Mi"s must all be crazy.

395
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,356
Sorry.

396
00:29:15,024 --> 00:29:16,317
Hang in there.

397
00:29:16,401 --> 00:29:19,612
I'm sure you'll have nothing
but good things ahead in your new place.

398
00:29:19,696 --> 00:29:23,116
Oh, and don't forget
to change the door lock code.

399
00:29:23,199 --> 00:29:24,200
Okay.

400
00:29:51,311 --> 00:29:52,145
Mr. Seo?

401
00:29:54,147 --> 00:29:56,232
Ms. Dam. You live here?

402
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:58,651
Yes, but…

403
00:29:58,735 --> 00:30:01,613
Mr. Cha sent me the address.

404
00:30:01,696 --> 00:30:03,406
I really didn't know.

405
00:30:03,489 --> 00:30:04,574
This is loud, isn't it?

406
00:30:05,533 --> 00:30:07,452
I must have pressed something wrong.

407
00:30:07,535 --> 00:30:08,369
Sorry.

408
00:30:10,663 --> 00:30:12,332
Do you need any help?

409
00:30:15,335 --> 00:30:16,210
Thank you.

410
00:30:16,294 --> 00:30:17,962
It was nothing.

411
00:30:18,046 --> 00:30:19,088
It wasn't nothing.

412
00:30:19,172 --> 00:30:21,507
I almost had to move out
as soon as I arrived.

413
00:30:21,591 --> 00:30:24,052
I've never seen you look
so flustered before.

414
00:30:24,719 --> 00:30:27,347
I didn't expect to see you here.

415
00:30:27,430 --> 00:30:28,973
You must've been even more shocked.

416
00:30:29,057 --> 00:30:30,808
I won't stay here long.

417
00:30:30,892 --> 00:30:33,227
Just for a while,
until things are wrapped up.

418
00:30:33,937 --> 00:30:34,938
I see.

419
00:30:35,021 --> 00:30:37,565
Let me treat you to something in return.

420
00:30:37,649 --> 00:30:38,650
Anything good nearby?

421
00:30:43,404 --> 00:30:46,115
In Korea, we have <i>jjajangmyeon</i>
on the day we move in.

422
00:30:46,199 --> 00:30:48,534
They say black food
chases away misfortune.

423
00:30:49,702 --> 00:30:51,287
You can mix it like this.

424
00:30:52,121 --> 00:30:53,373
I know how to do it.

425
00:30:55,667 --> 00:30:57,335
When did you come back to Seoul?

426
00:30:58,211 --> 00:30:59,754
It's been a while.

427
00:30:59,837 --> 00:31:01,881
I'm preparing for my return broadcast.

428
00:31:02,548 --> 00:31:04,342
Really? I'm glad you decided to return.

429
00:31:06,469 --> 00:31:08,596
How are those things
you said you were wrapping up?

430
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:12,100
I've only just gotten started.

431
00:31:12,934 --> 00:31:14,477
I've been avoiding it for a long time.

432
00:31:15,478 --> 00:31:17,814
I'm not sure what to do yet,

433
00:31:17,897 --> 00:31:20,483
but I'll just try, like you said before.

434
00:31:22,485 --> 00:31:25,571
Here's your scorching hot coffee.

435
00:31:25,655 --> 00:31:27,991
-It's really hot, right?
-Yes.

436
00:31:28,074 --> 00:31:30,076
Coffee should be hot.

437
00:31:32,328 --> 00:31:33,538
Gosh, that's hot!

438
00:31:34,664 --> 00:31:35,540
Hey!

439
00:31:36,457 --> 00:31:37,709
You wanted it hot…

440
00:31:42,714 --> 00:31:43,965
What about Eric?

441
00:31:44,716 --> 00:31:46,509
He's really going to stay in Korea?

442
00:31:49,429 --> 00:31:51,556
What could he possibly do anyway?

443
00:31:53,057 --> 00:31:55,852
How should I set up your office?

444
00:31:55,935 --> 00:31:57,562
Just the minimum.

445
00:31:57,645 --> 00:31:59,605
I'm just going to resolve
the raw material issue.

446
00:32:00,273 --> 00:32:01,399
Gojeuneok Bio

447
00:32:01,482 --> 00:32:04,485
was pretty firm
about not renewing the contract,

448
00:32:04,569 --> 00:32:06,529
so it won't be easy to convince them.

449
00:32:10,241 --> 00:32:11,951
I'm not wasting my time convincing them.

450
00:32:15,329 --> 00:32:17,582
CEO KANG MU-WON

451
00:32:18,499 --> 00:32:20,084
All our clients

452
00:32:20,168 --> 00:32:23,171
are suddenly canceling their contracts
as if it were coordinated.

453
00:32:23,713 --> 00:32:25,882
Even the ones that said
they'd only use our materials

454
00:32:25,965 --> 00:32:27,675
have suddenly gone silent.

455
00:32:28,551 --> 00:32:32,555
At this rate, we may have to get rid
of all the materials in our storage.

456
00:32:32,638 --> 00:32:33,639
You know that, right?

457
00:32:38,269 --> 00:32:39,270
But you know who I am.

458
00:32:40,313 --> 00:32:42,899
The god of sales, the devil of sales,
the ultimate salesman!

459
00:32:43,483 --> 00:32:44,734
Kang Mu-won.

460
00:32:45,651 --> 00:32:47,862
I booked a meeting with Hong Kong buyers.

461
00:32:49,322 --> 00:32:50,364
But…

462
00:32:52,033 --> 00:32:54,035
they want to meet you as well.

463
00:32:54,118 --> 00:32:56,621
They want to communicate in person.

464
00:32:58,206 --> 00:33:01,375
I know you hate meetings like this,

465
00:33:02,710 --> 00:33:04,629
but come with me, just this once.

466
00:33:05,171 --> 00:33:07,131
-If we miss this opportunity--
-I'll go.

467
00:33:08,382 --> 00:33:09,675
When is it?

468
00:33:31,364 --> 00:33:33,241
PERHAPS WE CAN SEE
THE RAINY SEASON TOGETHER

469
00:33:40,581 --> 00:33:41,791
TRY READING THIS

470
00:33:46,129 --> 00:33:47,588
<i>I don't like scribbling in books.</i>

471
00:33:48,214 --> 00:33:49,423
Scribbling?

472
00:33:49,507 --> 00:33:52,927
You're recording
where you felt your emotions.

473
00:33:53,511 --> 00:33:56,180
I was curious to see
which lines spoke to you.

474
00:33:56,264 --> 00:33:57,557
<i>Try marking them.</i>

475
00:34:04,981 --> 00:34:09,026
TRY READING THIS

476
00:34:42,268 --> 00:34:44,687
Hello, Ms. Dam.

477
00:34:45,188 --> 00:34:48,399
I'm Han Da-sol, the manager
of Selvanta Hotel &amp; Resorts' package.

478
00:34:48,482 --> 00:34:49,567
Nice to meet you, Ms. Han.

479
00:34:49,650 --> 00:34:52,945
Thank you for coming all this way
during your busy schedule.

480
00:34:53,029 --> 00:34:54,864
Of course, I had to come.

481
00:34:54,947 --> 00:34:57,825
Then we'll give you a tour.

482
00:34:57,909 --> 00:35:00,036
-All right.
-This way, please.

483
00:35:02,330 --> 00:35:03,873
GOJEUNEOK BIO

484
00:35:17,303 --> 00:35:19,764
This is Teramondo,
our all-day pub and bar.

485
00:35:19,847 --> 00:35:22,725
We serve a variety of finger foods

486
00:35:22,808 --> 00:35:26,520
to pair with drinks
from all around the world.

487
00:35:26,604 --> 00:35:29,774
A welcome drink
is a part of the package, right?

488
00:35:31,025 --> 00:35:33,569
This lounge is exclusively for our guests.

489
00:35:33,653 --> 00:35:35,196
They can hold business meetings

490
00:35:35,279 --> 00:35:37,823
as well as enjoy
beverages and snacks here.

491
00:35:37,907 --> 00:35:40,660
Can they access it anytime…

492
00:36:12,483 --> 00:36:13,901
Ms. Dam?

493
00:36:13,985 --> 00:36:15,194
-Yes?
-This way.

494
00:36:15,278 --> 00:36:16,404
Oh, right.

495
00:36:40,219 --> 00:36:41,470
Mechoori…

496
00:37:39,862 --> 00:37:42,281
So all of this was because of Ms. Dam.

497
00:37:43,949 --> 00:37:45,659
I saw you two earlier.

498
00:37:48,496 --> 00:37:50,081
I'd like to focus on work right now.

499
00:37:50,164 --> 00:37:52,958
Even if you focus,
just let me talk to you.

500
00:37:53,918 --> 00:37:57,296
I really can't keep watching you
shut yourself away.

501
00:37:57,380 --> 00:37:59,632
Stop avoiding the topic and talk to me.

502
00:38:00,633 --> 00:38:03,636
All right, fine. Take your time.

503
00:38:04,345 --> 00:38:06,514
I told you, what I have most after money

504
00:38:06,597 --> 00:38:08,182
is patience.

505
00:38:18,776 --> 00:38:21,237
I told Ms. Dam everything

506
00:38:22,029 --> 00:38:23,030
and ended things.

507
00:38:27,118 --> 00:38:31,247
When I first found out
you and Ms. Dam were dating,

508
00:38:31,330 --> 00:38:33,290
I was honestly pretty worried.

509
00:38:33,374 --> 00:38:34,417
But…

510
00:38:38,212 --> 00:38:41,799
for the first time in ages,
I saw the Hae-seok that I used to know.

511
00:38:45,219 --> 00:38:46,345
So I couldn't say anything.

512
00:38:49,348 --> 00:38:50,349
Mu-won.

513
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:54,812
I was being too selfish.

514
00:38:56,647 --> 00:39:00,317
I just hurt her
by starting that relationship.

515
00:39:00,860 --> 00:39:01,777
I'm not so sure.

516
00:39:02,736 --> 00:39:04,321
Could it be those thoughts of yours

517
00:39:04,405 --> 00:39:07,283
made Ms. Dam Ye-jin suffer
even more in the end?

518
00:39:10,077 --> 00:39:12,830
Didn't you let her go
because you didn't want her to feel hurt?

519
00:39:13,456 --> 00:39:15,291
But the look on her face earlier…

520
00:39:18,502 --> 00:39:19,712
You saw it too.

521
00:39:49,366 --> 00:39:51,076
MECHOORI

522
00:39:58,584 --> 00:40:00,586
<i>The person you are calling is unavailable.</i>

523
00:40:00,669 --> 00:40:04,423
<i>Please leave a message after the beep.</i>

524
00:40:05,633 --> 00:40:07,301
Let's talk.

525
00:40:09,678 --> 00:40:13,891
It might be over for you, Mechoori,

526
00:40:13,974 --> 00:40:16,143
but I still have more to say to you.

527
00:40:18,979 --> 00:40:20,940
So let's meet.

528
00:40:21,815 --> 00:40:24,193
Let's meet up and end things properly.

529
00:40:35,996 --> 00:40:38,916
MECHOORI

530
00:40:42,962 --> 00:40:44,380
Where are you?

531
00:40:44,463 --> 00:40:47,132
<i>Ms. Dam.</i>

532
00:40:47,883 --> 00:40:50,344
It's me, Park Kwang-mo.

533
00:40:52,137 --> 00:40:53,305
Mr. Park?

534
00:40:53,389 --> 00:40:57,726
<i>To be honest, this is my number.</i>

535
00:40:58,394 --> 00:41:02,690
You should hear
the full story from Mechoori.

536
00:41:04,108 --> 00:41:08,529
He wouldn't have used my number
for no reason.

537
00:41:09,863 --> 00:41:12,241
-Why…
<i>-Bye, then.</i>

538
00:41:24,878 --> 00:41:26,338
THIS IS MECHOORI'S NUMBER

539
00:41:29,717 --> 00:41:33,220
<i>Ye-jin. This is my number.</i>

540
00:41:33,804 --> 00:41:36,765
You can call me at this number
when you miss me.

541
00:41:45,441 --> 00:41:47,985
RECENT CALLS

542
00:41:48,068 --> 00:41:50,779
01:09 AM, OUTGOING CALL
00:38 AM, OUTGOING CALL

543
00:41:55,326 --> 00:41:58,370
01:11 AM, OUTGOING CALL
CALL RECORDING

544
00:41:58,454 --> 00:41:59,830
<i>-Hello?</i>
<i>-Mom.</i>

545
00:42:01,373 --> 00:42:03,542
<i>Mom, why weren't you picking up?</i>

546
00:42:04,084 --> 00:42:05,252
<i>Are you listening?</i>

547
00:42:08,922 --> 00:42:11,008
<i>You've called the wrong number.</i>

548
00:42:13,594 --> 00:42:14,595
<i>Mom?</i>

549
00:42:16,180 --> 00:42:18,474
<i>-Mom.</i>
<i>-If you call me one more time,</i>

550
00:42:18,557 --> 00:42:21,727
<i>I'm going to call the cops.</i>
<i>This is my last warning.</i>

551
00:42:22,853 --> 00:42:25,314
<i>-Look here.</i>
<i>-I miss you.</i>

552
00:42:25,397 --> 00:42:28,275
<i>I miss you, Mom.</i>

553
00:42:29,276 --> 00:42:31,236
<i>-Hello?</i>
<i>-Mom.</i>

554
00:42:31,862 --> 00:42:33,781
Excuse me. I clearly told you--

555
00:42:33,864 --> 00:42:35,032
<i>It's me, Ye-jin.</i>

556
00:42:35,616 --> 00:42:36,784
What?

557
00:42:36,867 --> 00:42:37,910
Who did you say you were?

558
00:42:37,993 --> 00:42:39,912
<i>Actually, I got hurt today.</i>

559
00:42:39,995 --> 00:42:42,247
Ms. Dam. Are you drunk?

560
00:42:42,331 --> 00:42:43,499
I'm hanging up.

561
00:42:45,709 --> 00:42:46,960
Hello?

562
00:42:47,711 --> 00:42:49,713
<i>Ms. Dam!</i>

563
00:42:50,673 --> 00:42:54,677
Would it be okay
to trust him instead of me

564
00:42:55,302 --> 00:42:57,680
and try this again?

565
00:42:58,764 --> 00:43:01,392
<i>-Mom.</i>
-Ms. Dam, where are you?

566
00:43:01,934 --> 00:43:03,977
Ms. Dam, can you hear me?

567
00:43:04,061 --> 00:43:05,562
Ms. Dam! Where are you right now?

568
00:43:06,730 --> 00:43:09,608
<i>Ms. Dam, can you hear me?</i>

569
00:43:09,692 --> 00:43:11,068
<i>Ms. Dam!</i>

570
00:43:13,237 --> 00:43:16,240
02:26 AM, OUTGOING CALL
CALL RECORDING

571
00:43:16,907 --> 00:43:19,076
<i>He said…</i>

572
00:43:19,159 --> 00:43:21,620
<i>that everything he showed me</i>

573
00:43:22,496 --> 00:43:25,290
<i>and all the moments we spent together</i>

574
00:43:25,374 --> 00:43:27,584
<i>were a lie.</i>

575
00:43:28,293 --> 00:43:30,337
<i>But</i>

576
00:43:30,421 --> 00:43:34,341
he seemed to be in more pain than me

577
00:43:35,759 --> 00:43:37,678
as he said that.

578
00:43:38,887 --> 00:43:40,514
I don't know.

579
00:43:42,766 --> 00:43:45,978
I have no idea…

580
00:43:46,770 --> 00:43:48,230
But…

581
00:43:49,857 --> 00:43:54,653
I want to hear what's really on his mind.

582
00:43:59,324 --> 00:44:01,034
<i>I wasn't lying.</i>

583
00:44:02,953 --> 00:44:04,413
<i>I was happy.</i>

584
00:44:07,583 --> 00:44:10,586
<i>While I was with you,</i>

585
00:44:13,380 --> 00:44:15,924
<i>I felt like I'd become a good person.</i>

586
00:44:17,384 --> 00:44:20,220
<i>And I even thought that perhaps</i>

587
00:44:20,304 --> 00:44:22,222
<i>nothing had happened to me.</i>

588
00:44:24,850 --> 00:44:26,393
But…

589
00:44:27,060 --> 00:44:28,729
I don't deserve this.

590
00:44:31,815 --> 00:44:33,233
I…

591
00:44:35,903 --> 00:44:38,655
killed a close friend
I trusted and admired.

592
00:44:40,657 --> 00:44:43,035
<i>Even when he took full responsibility</i>

593
00:44:43,702 --> 00:44:45,996
<i>and ended his life,</i>

594
00:44:47,623 --> 00:44:48,999
<i>I was hiding</i>

595
00:44:49,666 --> 00:44:52,211
<i>behind his shadow like a coward.</i>

596
00:44:53,587 --> 00:44:54,922
I was scared.

597
00:44:59,218 --> 00:45:02,137
I couldn't bring myself
to face him and our victims.

598
00:45:05,307 --> 00:45:07,226
But after I met you,

599
00:45:10,187 --> 00:45:11,522
I thought

600
00:45:13,857 --> 00:45:15,108
that perhaps…

601
00:45:19,613 --> 00:45:22,157
I could stand back up again

602
00:45:24,117 --> 00:45:25,577
for the first time.

603
00:45:27,996 --> 00:45:30,666
<i>I gained courage while I was with you.</i>

604
00:45:32,042 --> 00:45:34,002
<i>I felt like I could do it</i>

605
00:45:34,920 --> 00:45:36,922
<i>with you by my side.</i>

606
00:45:38,799 --> 00:45:40,884
<i>But I was being selfish.</i>

607
00:45:42,219 --> 00:45:44,972
<i>Even when I knew</i>
<i>how much it would hurt you,</i>

608
00:45:46,181 --> 00:45:47,683
<i>I still liked you.</i>

609
00:45:51,895 --> 00:45:52,980
I'm sorry.

610
00:45:56,149 --> 00:45:58,193
I'm sorry I came to love you

611
00:46:00,862 --> 00:46:02,823
when I couldn't even
take responsibility for it.

612
00:46:09,788 --> 00:46:10,872
And…

613
00:46:16,878 --> 00:46:18,380
I'm really grateful for everything.

614
00:46:40,986 --> 00:46:42,237
<i>I'll give you one each day.</i>

615
00:46:42,988 --> 00:46:45,574
Ms. Dam. Let's meet every day.

616
00:46:49,286 --> 00:46:51,997
Ms. Dam, what are you doing?
Didn't you hear the car?

617
00:46:52,080 --> 00:46:54,416
<i>Ms. Dam, where are you?</i>

618
00:46:54,499 --> 00:46:56,084
<i>Ms. Dam, where are you right now?</i>

619
00:46:56,168 --> 00:46:57,210
Ms. Dam.

620
00:46:57,294 --> 00:46:58,587
<i>Ms. Dam, can you hear me?</i>

621
00:46:58,670 --> 00:47:00,172
<i>Ms. Dam!</i>

622
00:47:27,699 --> 00:47:30,077
DAM YE-JIN

623
00:47:41,213 --> 00:47:42,214
Hello?

624
00:47:45,884 --> 00:47:46,885
Hello?

625
00:47:47,678 --> 00:47:50,430
Ms. Dam, where are you?

626
00:47:52,641 --> 00:47:55,060
Ms. Dam, can you hear me?

627
00:47:55,143 --> 00:47:56,353
<i>-I'm in the park.</i>
-Ms. Dam…

628
00:47:57,521 --> 00:47:58,772
<i>I'll wait for you.</i>

629
00:48:44,484 --> 00:48:47,279
Ms. Dam, are you okay?

630
00:48:47,362 --> 00:48:49,114
Are you hurt or anything?

631
00:48:49,197 --> 00:48:50,323
Let me see…

632
00:48:51,491 --> 00:48:53,076
Look at me.

633
00:48:56,246 --> 00:48:57,748
I knew it.

634
00:48:59,166 --> 00:49:01,209
I knew you'd come running over.

635
00:49:10,469 --> 00:49:11,928
I'll go now.

636
00:49:12,971 --> 00:49:14,765
I heard everything.

637
00:49:17,642 --> 00:49:20,771
I heard how I called you every night,

638
00:49:22,481 --> 00:49:24,816
crying and calling my mom.

639
00:49:25,901 --> 00:49:26,902
And…

640
00:49:29,112 --> 00:49:31,448
I heard what you said as well.

641
00:49:36,787 --> 00:49:39,039
It must have been
so hard for you, all alone.

642
00:49:40,582 --> 00:49:42,042
I know how it feels.

643
00:49:42,125 --> 00:49:44,920
So I can't just leave you alone.

644
00:49:50,050 --> 00:49:51,718
Are you stupid?

645
00:49:52,803 --> 00:49:54,054
Do you still not get it?

646
00:49:55,847 --> 00:49:58,391
All those painful times

647
00:49:59,267 --> 00:50:01,520
you had to go through…

648
00:50:03,980 --> 00:50:05,315
It was all because of me.

649
00:50:06,191 --> 00:50:07,776
If it wasn't for me…

650
00:50:08,985 --> 00:50:10,487
Stop.

651
00:50:11,905 --> 00:50:13,240
Don't say that.

652
00:50:16,827 --> 00:50:18,954
You took all my calls

653
00:50:19,037 --> 00:50:21,623
because you couldn't bear
to leave me alone either.

654
00:50:23,875 --> 00:50:25,710
I feel the same way.

655
00:50:39,808 --> 00:50:41,601
Just stay by my side.

656
00:50:44,020 --> 00:50:46,356
I'll stay by your side too.

657
00:51:35,322 --> 00:51:37,198
I'll check that again.

658
00:51:42,162 --> 00:51:43,997
It seems like you slept well.

659
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:46,750
How about a spa after our meeting?

660
00:51:51,922 --> 00:51:53,173
What? Who are you…

661
00:51:57,636 --> 00:51:58,553
You found the courage.

662
00:51:58,637 --> 00:52:00,347
Did you eat?

663
00:52:01,306 --> 00:52:03,016
-Yes, I did.
-He did.

664
00:52:04,476 --> 00:52:05,560
Good luck with the meeting!

665
00:52:07,979 --> 00:52:09,856
I'll call you later.

666
00:52:13,735 --> 00:52:14,569
Oh, my.

667
00:52:18,198 --> 00:52:20,533
Just go and talk to her.

668
00:52:20,617 --> 00:52:22,535
Our meeting's about to start.

669
00:52:23,495 --> 00:52:24,496
Sorry.

670
00:52:37,425 --> 00:52:39,552
Should I knock on their door?
I know the room number.

671
00:52:40,887 --> 00:52:41,888
Let's wait a bit more.

672
00:52:43,515 --> 00:52:44,975
It's already been 40 minutes.

673
00:52:45,058 --> 00:52:46,518
This must be something serious.

674
00:52:47,185 --> 00:52:48,687
I'll try calling them one more time.

675
00:52:49,312 --> 00:52:51,606
It didn't seem like
they were just sounding us out.

676
00:53:12,419 --> 00:53:14,004
Ms. Michelle…

677
00:53:16,840 --> 00:53:18,675
We haven't met before.

678
00:53:18,758 --> 00:53:20,468
Nice to meet you. I'm Michelle.

679
00:53:24,639 --> 00:53:26,349
You must be happy to see me.

680
00:53:41,906 --> 00:53:43,825
WHITE FLOWER NOORI MUSHROOM
PURCHASE AGREEMENT

681
00:53:44,409 --> 00:53:46,745
This is the last option for Gojeuneok.

682
00:53:46,828 --> 00:53:50,248
I sent your previous option
back to Hong Kong.

683
00:53:51,499 --> 00:53:55,628
We've made our position clear
to Mr. Eric Seo.

684
00:53:57,422 --> 00:53:58,381
Eric.

685
00:53:58,465 --> 00:54:00,550
He must have forgotten to mention that

686
00:54:00,633 --> 00:54:03,428
since he was packing his stuff in a hurry.

687
00:54:03,511 --> 00:54:06,264
Gojeuneok will not be signing
a contract with L'Étoile again.

688
00:54:06,347 --> 00:54:09,642
But Gojeuneok won't be signing
with any other company either.

689
00:54:09,726 --> 00:54:12,020
Most of them tread carefully around me.

690
00:54:13,188 --> 00:54:15,273
Then send the signed contract
through Mr. Cha.

691
00:54:15,356 --> 00:54:16,524
Don't drag this out.

692
00:54:18,151 --> 00:54:19,694
Gojeuneok

693
00:54:20,278 --> 00:54:21,946
will not sign another contract

694
00:54:23,948 --> 00:54:24,949
with L'Étoile.

695
00:54:27,494 --> 00:54:30,246
All right. Take your time to think.

696
00:54:30,330 --> 00:54:32,957
And there's no need to repeat yourself.

697
00:54:33,041 --> 00:54:34,834
I speak Korean fluently.

698
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:53,603
All the buyers who kept in touch
are ignoring my calls now.

699
00:54:54,646 --> 00:54:58,358
I did think it was strange
when our clients canceled our contracts.

700
00:54:58,441 --> 00:55:01,152
How far did L'Étoile actually go?

701
00:55:01,236 --> 00:55:03,363
If this drags on any longer,
it could get risky.

702
00:55:05,824 --> 00:55:07,575
Whether it's in Korea or abroad,

703
00:55:07,659 --> 00:55:11,079
check all seminar and expo schedules
where we can meet buyers.

704
00:55:12,330 --> 00:55:14,499
I'm sure we'll find an opportunity.

705
00:55:14,582 --> 00:55:15,625
All right.

706
00:55:16,835 --> 00:55:18,086
GOJEUNEOK BIO

707
00:55:19,295 --> 00:55:21,172
HIT HOMESHOPPING

708
00:55:24,384 --> 00:55:25,760
<i>I can't make it.</i>

709
00:55:26,553 --> 00:55:28,096
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

710
00:55:28,930 --> 00:55:29,931
Is it Mr. Proper?

711
00:55:30,014 --> 00:55:31,099
Yes.

712
00:55:32,767 --> 00:55:34,060
But what's wrong?

713
00:55:35,019 --> 00:55:37,188
You were so happy about dating again.

714
00:55:37,814 --> 00:55:39,524
Did he say he can't make it today?

715
00:55:40,108 --> 00:55:41,860
He said something came up.

716
00:55:44,362 --> 00:55:47,073
Why on earth is he so busy?

717
00:55:47,157 --> 00:55:49,033
Is he just going to work forever?

718
00:55:50,785 --> 00:55:53,288
Are you talking about yourself?

719
00:56:17,896 --> 00:56:20,148
WHITE FLOWER NOORI MUSHROOM
PURCHASE AGREEMENT

720
00:56:28,740 --> 00:56:30,491
Four years ago,

721
00:56:30,575 --> 00:56:33,536
when I suggested starting over…

722
00:56:35,079 --> 00:56:37,207
remember how I promised

723
00:56:37,290 --> 00:56:40,960
I'd let you hold on to your principles
until the end?

724
00:56:44,130 --> 00:56:45,798
It's not over yet.

725
00:56:51,471 --> 00:56:52,472
It is.

726
00:56:58,728 --> 00:56:59,729
No more hesitation!

727
00:57:03,650 --> 00:57:05,443
Lee Hae-seok!

728
00:57:06,861 --> 00:57:07,946
Chang-ho.

729
00:57:11,532 --> 00:57:13,493
You little brat.

730
00:57:13,576 --> 00:57:15,662
How can you not give me a single call?

731
00:57:16,496 --> 00:57:18,456
How have you been?

732
00:57:18,539 --> 00:57:19,457
What…

733
00:57:20,208 --> 00:57:24,254
Right. This is still a formal meeting.
We need an official introduction.

734
00:57:24,337 --> 00:57:26,339
Say hello to the CEO of H.O. Cosmetics,

735
00:57:26,422 --> 00:57:29,551
which is growing fast
across Thailand and Southeast Asia.

736
00:57:29,634 --> 00:57:32,095
Mr. Son Chang-ho.

737
00:57:32,178 --> 00:57:33,763
Hey, you're making me blush.

738
00:57:33,846 --> 00:57:36,641
What happened? How did you…

739
00:57:36,724 --> 00:57:39,185
I contacted Mu-won.

740
00:57:40,019 --> 00:57:43,106
I heard rumors
that L'Étoile's been pressuring you,

741
00:57:43,189 --> 00:57:44,482
and I couldn't just sit still.

742
00:57:45,441 --> 00:57:47,986
H.O. Cosmetics
isn't scared of L'Étoile, you know.

743
00:57:48,695 --> 00:57:50,238
His business reflects his personality.

744
00:57:51,489 --> 00:57:53,616
I think business suits me better.

745
00:57:53,700 --> 00:57:56,369
Don't I look much better
than when I was cooped up in the lab?

746
00:57:57,787 --> 00:57:58,871
You do.

747
00:58:11,175 --> 00:58:12,176
Ms. Dam.

748
00:58:15,138 --> 00:58:16,639
Who were you again?

749
00:58:22,020 --> 00:58:23,813
I'm sorry. Something came up at work.

750
00:58:24,731 --> 00:58:25,732
What was it?

751
00:58:28,234 --> 00:58:29,319
It's been resolved.

752
00:58:29,902 --> 00:58:32,238
I didn't even know.

753
00:58:32,322 --> 00:58:35,241
I was upset that you weren't
messaging me much today.

754
00:58:36,117 --> 00:58:37,869
-I'm sorry.
-Is that it?

755
00:58:39,871 --> 00:58:41,289
I'll treat you to something nice.

756
00:58:42,540 --> 00:58:44,751
You'd better take me to a fancy place.

757
00:58:45,835 --> 00:58:46,669
Shall we go, then?

758
00:58:47,253 --> 00:58:49,505
Let me just go change my shoes.
My feet hurt.

759
00:58:57,639 --> 00:58:58,473
Ms. Dam.

760
00:58:59,432 --> 00:59:00,642
Mr. Seo.

761
00:59:04,771 --> 00:59:06,481
What are you doing here?

762
00:59:06,564 --> 00:59:08,941
Oh, I live here.

763
00:59:09,025 --> 00:59:10,860
I live next door to Ms. Dam.

764
00:59:13,696 --> 00:59:15,531
-Head inside.
-Okay.

765
00:59:26,459 --> 00:59:28,461
Well, Mr. Seo…

766
00:59:30,630 --> 00:59:32,882
You said you'll change your shoes.

767
00:59:32,965 --> 00:59:33,841
Go ahead.

768
00:59:35,343 --> 00:59:36,844
I'll be back in a second.

769
00:59:40,765 --> 00:59:41,974
I won't be long.

770
00:59:51,526 --> 00:59:53,736
THE DAY HE FOUND OUT ERIC
LIVES NEXT DOOR TO YE-JIN

771
00:59:53,820 --> 00:59:55,947
<i>That was a romantic story.</i>

772
00:59:56,030 --> 00:59:58,991
<i>I hope things go well with your neighbor.</i>

773
00:59:59,075 --> 01:00:00,660
<i>Let's listen to the song you requested.</i>

774
01:00:00,743 --> 01:00:01,786
<i>Olive, You Too's</i>

775
01:00:01,869 --> 01:00:04,747
<i>"I Can't Forget the Pizza</i>
<i>I had with My Neighbor."</i>

776
01:00:04,831 --> 01:00:07,333
<i>Can't forget… Neighbor…</i>

777
01:00:07,417 --> 01:00:09,794
<i>I live next door to Ms. Dam.</i>

778
01:00:13,131 --> 01:00:17,677
I can't eat all this by myself.
What do I do?

779
01:00:24,642 --> 01:00:27,061
Then you can share it
with your neighbor, no?

780
01:00:32,275 --> 01:00:34,110
Mr. Seo.

781
01:00:45,580 --> 01:00:46,748
Neighbor?

782
01:00:48,708 --> 01:00:50,376
Let's just go to the place next door.

783
01:00:50,460 --> 01:00:52,253
THE SECOND DAY HE FOUND OUT

784
01:00:52,336 --> 01:00:54,005
-Next door?
-Yes, their food's great.

785
01:00:54,088 --> 01:00:55,256
Let's go.

786
01:01:00,344 --> 01:01:01,387
Oh, no!

787
01:01:01,471 --> 01:01:03,514
There's a spider!

788
01:01:09,771 --> 01:01:11,189
You can rely on me.

789
01:01:16,152 --> 01:01:17,612
Mr. Seo…

790
01:01:19,322 --> 01:01:21,032
Hey. Come on, baby.

791
01:01:21,115 --> 01:01:22,909
-No!
-What do you mean?

792
01:01:22,992 --> 01:01:24,035
Come on. It'll take ages.

793
01:01:24,118 --> 01:01:25,536
-I'm hungry.
-I'm not going!

794
01:01:26,704 --> 01:01:27,872
This is the problem with you.

795
01:01:28,456 --> 01:01:30,082
Why are you so impatient?

796
01:01:30,166 --> 01:01:31,709
You wanted to eat here.

797
01:01:31,793 --> 01:01:33,419
You said this place is good!

798
01:01:33,503 --> 01:01:35,171
Why would you go next door?

799
01:01:35,254 --> 01:01:36,130
I'm not going!

800
01:01:38,341 --> 01:01:40,468
Thanks for changing the bulbs for us.

801
01:01:40,551 --> 01:01:43,763
I used to change the bulbs all the time,
even for my neighbors.

802
01:01:43,846 --> 01:01:44,931
Who would ask you for help?

803
01:01:45,014 --> 01:01:46,516
Hey, my neighbors loved me…

804
01:01:49,894 --> 01:01:52,355
Oh, no! Is this a blackout?

805
01:01:52,438 --> 01:01:53,731
What do I do?

806
01:02:01,906 --> 01:02:03,741
Don't you worry.

807
01:02:03,825 --> 01:02:04,867
Your neighbor is here.

808
01:02:05,827 --> 01:02:07,328
Mr. Seo…

809
01:02:11,582 --> 01:02:12,583
Neighbor.

810
01:02:13,793 --> 01:02:14,794
Neighbor.

811
01:02:17,922 --> 01:02:19,298
I almost dislocated my shoulder.

812
01:02:19,382 --> 01:02:20,591
You can't do it.

813
01:02:20,675 --> 01:02:23,094
How long do I have
to keep doing stuff like this?

814
01:02:25,721 --> 01:02:27,473
I'm not doing this anymore.

815
01:02:28,015 --> 01:02:28,891
Handle it yourself.

816
01:02:28,975 --> 01:02:30,685
What's gotten into him?

817
01:02:30,768 --> 01:02:32,061
What's with him?

818
01:02:32,144 --> 01:02:33,521
Oh, right. Mechoori!

819
01:02:33,604 --> 01:02:34,897
The people next door need--

820
01:02:35,731 --> 01:02:38,234
Has he lost his mind?
Our neighbors need their light fixed too.

821
01:02:41,946 --> 01:02:42,822
That's so nice.

822
01:02:42,905 --> 01:02:44,031
You look beautiful.

823
01:02:44,740 --> 01:02:47,743
Let's wear white heels.
What about your jewelry?

824
01:02:47,827 --> 01:02:48,661
Let's see.

825
01:02:48,744 --> 01:02:50,454
I want to wear this.

826
01:02:58,671 --> 01:03:00,673
What?

827
01:03:00,756 --> 01:03:01,632
It's so pretty.

828
01:03:01,716 --> 01:03:03,759
-Right?
-You'll shine on screen.

829
01:03:03,843 --> 01:03:05,887
It's my first broadcast after returning.

830
01:03:05,970 --> 01:03:07,430
I need something special.

831
01:03:07,513 --> 01:03:08,848
It's gorgeous.

832
01:03:08,931 --> 01:03:11,684
Everyone, were you looking for me?

833
01:03:11,767 --> 01:03:14,061
This is exactly the kind of broadcast
you need right now.

834
01:03:14,145 --> 01:03:17,106
I've returned after a long time
with Selvanta Hotel and Resorts'

835
01:03:17,189 --> 01:03:20,610
hotel vacation package
that will satisfy your needs.

836
01:03:20,693 --> 01:03:21,652
This is Dam Ye-jin.

837
01:03:21,736 --> 01:03:24,155
I'm sure some of you

838
01:03:24,238 --> 01:03:26,490
<i>feel burdened</i>
<i>by the thought of going abroad,</i>

839
01:03:26,574 --> 01:03:28,826
<i>but don't want to just stay at home.</i>

840
01:03:28,910 --> 01:03:31,370
<i>If you want to enjoy a proper vacation</i>
<i>during a short break…</i>

841
01:03:31,454 --> 01:03:32,997
Mu-won, do you like hotel vacations?

842
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:34,457
CEO KANG MU-WON

843
01:03:34,540 --> 01:03:35,958
Mu-won?

844
01:03:36,042 --> 01:03:37,501
I love them.

845
01:03:37,585 --> 01:03:38,628
You scared me.

846
01:03:41,631 --> 01:03:43,966
-What do you think?
-The two of us?

847
01:03:51,223 --> 01:03:54,101
CEO LEE HAE-SEOK

848
01:04:00,524 --> 01:04:03,402
Why would you bulk-buy
hotel vacation packages?

849
01:04:03,486 --> 01:04:05,905
I'll be doing a broadcast every day.
Will you buy everything?

850
01:04:05,988 --> 01:04:07,573
I have lots of money.

851
01:04:16,248 --> 01:04:18,334
Get some sleep, Mechoori.

852
01:04:18,417 --> 01:04:20,002
No, I'm fine.

853
01:04:20,586 --> 01:04:21,796
Aren't you going to sleep?

854
01:04:23,965 --> 01:04:26,008
Well, don't nag me.

855
01:04:27,426 --> 01:04:30,221
But I can't sleep deeply these days.

856
01:04:31,055 --> 01:04:32,264
I wake easily from my sleep.

857
01:04:35,685 --> 01:04:36,686
Since when?

858
01:04:38,938 --> 01:04:40,189
Since I came back to Seoul.

859
01:04:41,148 --> 01:04:43,901
<i>Maybe it was the clear water</i>
<i>or the air there,</i>

860
01:04:43,985 --> 01:04:45,569
<i>but I got much better…</i>

861
01:04:47,029 --> 01:04:48,823
Maybe it's because I'm alone here.

862
01:04:51,409 --> 01:04:52,827
Just saying.

863
01:04:52,910 --> 01:04:55,663
I've been cutting back on coffee,
so I'll get better soon.

864
01:05:14,974 --> 01:05:16,392
You haven't slept yet?

865
01:05:16,934 --> 01:05:18,185
<i>Will you come outside?</i>

866
01:05:21,689 --> 01:05:23,566
What? What's going on?

867
01:05:30,573 --> 01:05:31,907
Mechoori!

868
01:05:33,451 --> 01:05:34,660
Let me sleep over.

869
01:05:35,661 --> 01:05:36,495
What?

870
01:05:37,455 --> 01:05:38,664
Let's sleep together.

871
01:05:48,424 --> 01:05:52,011
SOLD OUT ON YOU

872
01:05:52,094 --> 01:05:54,889
THANKS TO SPECIAL GUEST SEO HYUN-WOO

873
01:06:26,629 --> 01:06:27,630
<i>Come here.</i>

874
01:06:27,713 --> 01:06:29,381
<i>Hurry up and sleep.</i>

875
01:06:30,091 --> 01:06:31,550
<i>Are you a chef?</i>

876
01:06:31,634 --> 01:06:34,970
<i>The person you cook for</i>
<i>would be really happy.</i>

877
01:06:35,054 --> 01:06:36,972
Is this what they call
a deep, savory flavor?

878
01:06:37,056 --> 01:06:38,682
This is really delicious, sir.

879
01:06:39,642 --> 01:06:40,768
-Ms. Dam!
-Sweetie!

880
01:06:40,851 --> 01:06:42,853
<i>Is your workplace far from here?</i>

881
01:06:42,937 --> 01:06:45,272
<i>Can you show us around?</i>

882
01:06:45,356 --> 01:06:46,816
Let me introduce

883
01:06:46,899 --> 01:06:49,610
Sollen's steady collection
of men's jackets.

884
01:06:51,612 --> 01:06:53,155
This is our last rent.

885
01:06:53,239 --> 01:06:54,740
I'm going to Seoul with Som-yi.

886
01:06:54,824 --> 01:06:57,368
No! I don't want to live with you.

887
01:06:57,451 --> 01:06:58,869
<i>What do I do?</i>

888
01:06:58,953 --> 01:07:00,955
<i>-Som-yi's missing.</i>
-Na Som-yi!

889
01:07:09,046 --> 01:07:11,048
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

